âœ… Requirements
Functional:
A user can add/remove/update items in the cart.

A user can view the current state of their cart.

Each cart is associated with one user.

Support quantity updates for existing items.

Persist cart items temporarily (guest) and permanently (logged-in users).


Non-Functional:
Should be highly available and responsive.

Should support millions of users in parallel.

Sync with inventory system for item availability.



Further extensions:

Extend this with promo codes & discounts?

Add concurrency control for real-time updates?

Build a REST API or Kafka-based version?


